    {
        "url": "/quotes/romesh_gunesekera_734382",
        "quote": "Every Sri Lankan, and almost every visitor to Sri Lanka, carries a longing for the place in some small form - hiraeth, the Welsh call it - wherever they go and whatever their background. It binds them however much the war and politics might try to divide them.",
